HEADWORD: good-king-henry
<hw>good-king-henry</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A European plant
(<spn>Chenopodium bonus-henricus</spn>) naturalized in North America;
often collected from the wild as a potherb.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> good king henry, allgood, fat hen, wild spinach,
<spn>Chenopodium bonus-henricus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
